      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm struggling with a shopify theme. on mobile the product image is totally overlapping the title and description, it looks like a mess. i checked the css but cant see why it's happening on small screens. \n\nhere is the snippet i'm working with:\n\n.product-single__media {\n  float: left;\n  width: 50%;\n}\n\n.product-single__info {\n  float: right;\n  width: 50%;\n}\n\nany idea why this is breaking on mobile?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the problem lies in the way the floating elements are behaving, as they don't always play nicely with the mobile browsers' layout engines. It's a common issue with the float property, especially when dealing with smaller screens and the need for responsive design. \n\nYou might want to try using flexbox instead, as it's more flexible and better suited for creating responsive layouts. Here's an example of how you can refactor your CSS to use flexbox:\n\n```css\n.product-single__media, .product-single__info {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  width: 100%;\n}\n\n.product-single__media {\n  flex: 1;\n}\n\n.product-single__info {\n  flex: 1;\n}\n```\n\nThis should help you avoid the overlapping issue on mobile devices. Remember, when working with CSS, it's often helpful to use a mobile-first approach, where you design for smaller screens first and then gradually increase the layout for larger screens using media queries. This way, you'll ensure that your theme looks good on all devices. \n\nAlso, don't forget to check your theme's responsiveness by using the browser's developer tools. They can help you identify any issues that might be causing the overlap on mobile devices. Good luck, and",
      "source": "target",
